cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NA 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of semantic 3D reconstruction, which involves labeling and regularization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of anisotropic and non-metric regularizers, which suggests that it may belong to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of functional lifting and convex relaxation techniques indicates that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
